  "text": "Pen size has been commonly used as a predictor of animal value [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . Typically, buyers prefer larger lots and lots with heifers bred to the same sire, and they pay the highest prices during the midpoint of the sale [CITATION_7] .",
